From: Ra Project <ra@example.com>
Date: 2026-05-14
Subject: [PATCH] Add raw_parser_hook to PostgreSQL 19

Add a raw_parser_hook extension point to the PostgreSQL parser.

The parser is the only stage in the query pipeline without a hook:
  raw_parser -> (no hook) -> analyze -> rewrite -> plan -> execute

All other stages have hooks (post_parse_analyze_hook, planner_hook,
ProcessUtility_hook, ExecutorStart_hook, etc.).  This patch fills that
gap by allowing extensions to intercept or replace the raw parser.

Semantics:
  - NULL return from hook = fall through to standard raw_parser()
  - Non-NULL return = use the returned parse tree directly
  - Zero overhead when hook is NULL (single pointer comparison)

Follows existing PostgreSQL hook patterns (planner_hook,
ProcessUtility_hook): a global function pointer initialized to NULL,
checked at the top of the hooked function, set by extensions in
_PG_init().

---
 src/backend/parser/parser.c  | 14 ++++++++++++++
 src/include/parser/parser.h  |  6 ++++++
 2 files changed, 20 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/include/parser/parser.h b/src/include/parser/parser.h
index aabbccdd..eeff0011 100644
--- a/src/include/parser/parser.h
+++ b/src/include/parser/parser.h
@@ -33,6 +33,12 @@ typedef enum

 extern List *raw_parser(const char *str, RawParseMode mode);

+/* Hook for extensions to replace the raw parser */
+typedef List *(*raw_parser_hook_type)(const char *query_string,
+									  RawParseMode mode);
+extern PGDLLIMPORT raw_parser_hook_type raw_parser_hook;
+
+
 extern List *SystemFuncName(char *name);
 extern TypeName *SystemTypeName(char *name);

diff --git a/src/backend/parser/parser.c b/src/backend/parser/parser.c
index aabbccdd..eeff0011 100644
--- a/src/backend/parser/parser.c
+++ b/src/backend/parser/parser.c
@@ -36,6 +36,10 @@
 static bool check_uescapechar(unsigned char escape);
 static char *str_udeescape(const char *str, char escape,
 						   int position, core_yyscan_t yyscanner);
+
+/* Hook for replacing the raw parser */
+raw_parser_hook_type raw_parser_hook = NULL;
+

 /*
  * raw_parser
@@ -48,6 +52,16 @@ List *
 raw_parser(const char *str, RawParseMode mode)
 {
 	core_yyscan_t yyscanner;
+
+	/* Allow extension to replace parser */
+	if (raw_parser_hook)
+	{
+		List	   *result = (*raw_parser_hook)(str, mode);
+
+		if (result != NULL)
+			return result;
+		/* NULL = fall through to standard parser */
+	}
+
 	base_yyscan_t yyscanner_extra;
 	int			yyresult;
 	List	   *raw_parsetree_list;
